        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-23 00:33:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nDi, the use of \"f_oid = 0\" is what is causing the 2.1 clients to fail.\n\nTo be honest, I'd prefer that \"fid_oid(fid) != 0\" be returned to fid_is_sane(), and only add an exception for the osd-ldiskfs and osd-zfs paths that need to deal with fid_is_last_id() (I guess osd_fid_lookup()?)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
