        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-24 19:59:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAndreas, set root _fid oi to 1 will let fid_is_last_id return false(thanks for pointing out the problem), which is exactly what we want. Besides, fid_is_last_id only check idif, normal and echo fid now. \n\n/* Check whether the fid is for LAST_ID */\nstatic inline int fid_is_last_id(const struct lu_fid *fid)\n{\n        return (fid_is_idif(fid) || fid_is_norm(fid) || fid_is_echo(fid)) &&\n                fid_oid(fid) == 0;\n}\n\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
