      "date": "2013-01-27 20:09:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nprobably I missed something, but what is wrong with using FID_SEQ_SPECIAL? Comments say like client may think all fids in that sequence are on the same server but what is an exception?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "e4bc25c36ad440464c4ce38e49ea45f04700b865",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-28 04:16:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nOh, we currently use SPECIAL_SEQUENCE for BFL and ROOT FID right now. BUT in phase I, BFL will be always local for each MDT, but ROOT FID will only on MDT0, so we can not put them in the same sequence, because of  fld only cache sequence.  and also if we bond root fid with special seq , it means all other vids under this seq will be bond to mdt0.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
